\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces $\alpha $ trajectories (top) and corresponding reward curves (bottom) for peg-insert-side-v3 (left, 12 seeds) and pick-place-v3 (right, 12 seeds). Warm lines indicate ever-solved seeds (including 3 DTF seeds on pick-place); dark blue dashed lines indicate $\alpha $-collapse; purple dashed lines indicate $\alpha $-explosion. On both tasks, ever-solved seeds maintain $\alpha $ in the shaded stable zone [0.01, 0.30], while never-solved seeds diverge to extreme values. The $\alpha $ bifurcation is visible by $\sim $200k steps, substantially earlier than reward differences emerge.}}{4}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:bifurcation}{{1}{4}{$\alpha $ trajectories (top) and corresponding reward curves (bottom) for peg-insert-side-v3 (left, 12 seeds) and pick-place-v3 (right, 12 seeds). Warm lines indicate ever-solved seeds (including 3 DTF seeds on pick-place); dark blue dashed lines indicate $\alpha $-collapse; purple dashed lines indicate $\alpha $-explosion. On both tasks, ever-solved seeds maintain $\alpha $ in the shaded stable zone [0.01, 0.30], while never-solved seeds diverge to extreme values. The $\alpha $ bifurcation is visible by $\sim $200k steps, substantially earlier than reward differences emerge}{figure.1}{}}
