\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Per-task summary across all experimental runs. $\alpha $ statistics are computed from exp.~36 (observational study). Reward statistics are mean $\pm $ std across seeds at final checkpoint. $\dagger $~denotes 12-seed runs. Solve rate counts seeds that ever achieve episode reward $\geq 500$ during training; three pick-place seeds (4, 10, 11) discover then forget the solution (DTF).}}{5}{table.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:summary}{{3}{5}{Per-task summary across all experimental runs. $\alpha $ statistics are computed from exp.~36 (observational study). Reward statistics are mean $\pm $ std across seeds at final checkpoint. $\dagger $~denotes 12-seed runs. Solve rate counts seeds that ever achieve episode reward $\geq 500$ during training; three pick-place seeds (4, 10, 11) discover then forget the solution (DTF)}{table.3}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Three failure modes identified from $\alpha $ trajectories (pick-place-v3). (a)~$\alpha $-collapse: entropy coefficient decays to near-zero before task discovery, trapping the policy in a local minimum. (b)~$\alpha $-explosion: entropy term grows to dominate the objective, preventing policy commitment. (c)~Discover-then-forget: $\alpha $ remains in the healthy range but the policy catastrophically loses a learned solution (reward spike at step 891k). Modes (a) and (b) are detectable from $\alpha $ alone; mode (c) requires joint monitoring.}}{5}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:failure_modes}{{2}{5}{Three failure modes identified from $\alpha $ trajectories (pick-place-v3). (a)~$\alpha $-collapse: entropy coefficient decays to near-zero before task discovery, trapping the policy in a local minimum. (b)~$\alpha $-explosion: entropy term grows to dominate the objective, preventing policy commitment. (c)~Discover-then-forget: $\alpha $ remains in the healthy range but the policy catastrophically loses a learned solution (reward spike at step 891k). Modes (a) and (b) are detectable from $\alpha $ alone; mode (c) requires joint monitoring}{figure.2}{}}
